After 13 years of work she still owes the Iowa School of Beauty by way of her creditors more than $8,000.
When I was a writing tutor at one of our directional state universities years ago, I often assisted nursing students.
But they put up with it for the very simple reason that they all wanted one thing: to help people.
This is true, among other reasons, because it is not at all clear that the ability to earn high grades in what is essentially a pre-medical school curriculum is the most important quality in a prospective nurse.
In the 1940s the United States and Britain managed to train hundreds of thousands of nurses virtually overnight with nothing but practical, on-the-job training.